<paragraph blockId="9.[146,245,1449,1473]" box="[146,245,1449,1473]" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">
<emphasis box="[146,245,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[146,1103,1489,1706]" lastBlockId="10.[213,1169,167,543]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="921" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">
This is a well known species associated with fouling organisms, preferring areas with relatively fast flowing waters. 
<collectingCountry box="[506,647,1522,1546]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
is its type locality (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson W" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" pagination="1 - 240" refId="ref6441" refString="Stimpson W. 1907. Report on the Crustacea (Brachyura and Anomura) collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition 1853 - 1856. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections 49: 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="1907">Stimpson 1907</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species is currently recognized in the current literature, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[995,1102,1554,1578]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">S. nitidus</emphasis>
Stimpson, 1858
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[366,686,1586,1610]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[366,499,1586,1610]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">Sphaerozius</emphasis>
Stimpson, 1858
</taxonomicName>
, but indications are that there are at least two taxa. Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[574,671,1618,1642]" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">syntypes</typeStatus>
of one of the purported synonyms, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1798" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[146,503,1650,1674]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scaber">
<emphasis box="[146,308,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">Cancer scaber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius JC" box="[321,503,1650,1674]" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" refId="ref4737" refString="Fabricius JC. 1798. Supplementum Entomologiae Systematicae Hafniae: Proft et Storch 572 p." type="book" year="1798">Fabricius, 1798</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in ZMUC (1 
<emphasis box="[687,705,1651,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">„</emphasis>
, 15.5× 
<quantity box="[798,897,1650,1674]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" unit="mm" value="12.3">12.3 mm</quantity>
, Cru 112-4; 1 
<emphasis box="[1078,1096,1651,1674]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="920">„</emphasis>
, 18.0×14.0 mm, Cru 112-1; 
<specimenCount box="[475,516,1681,1706]" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
, 18.4× 
<quantity box="[610,708,1682,1706]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.42" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" unit="mm" value="14.2">14.2 mm</quantity>
, Cru 112-2; 
<specimenCount box="[866,906,1681,1706]" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
, 18.4× 
<quantity box="[1000,1098,1682,1706]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.42" pageId="9" pageNumber="920" unit="mm" value="14.2">14.2 mm</quantity>
, 112-3; 
<specimenCount box="[289,324,167,192]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
, 17.7× 
<quantity box="[413,511,168,192]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
, Cru 112-5; ‘‘ 
<collectingCountry box="[662,726,168,192]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">India</collectingCountry>
Orientali’’, Dom. Daldorff) suggests it is a distinct species, distinguished most easily by its far more granulose carapace. For this present study a good series of specimens was examined and these are referable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[213,326,264,288]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[213,326,264,288]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">S. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[423,540,263,287]" name="Singapore" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[562,666,263,287]" name="Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[860,933,263,287]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai K" box="[953,1112,263,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref6036" refString="Sakai K. 1999 a. J. F. W. Herbst-Collection of Decapod Crustacea of the Berlin Zoological Museum, with remarks on certain species. Naturalists, Tokushima Biological. Laboratory 6: 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="1999">Sakai (1999a</bibRefCitation>
, 31) recognised 
<taxonomicName authority="(Herbst, 1801)" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[341,733,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panope">
<emphasis box="[341,561,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Sphaerozius panope</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Herbst JFW" box="[577,725,295,319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="1 - 46" refId="ref5066" refString="Herbst JFW. 1801. Versuch einer Naturgeschichte der Krabben und Krebse, nebst einer systematischen Beschreibung ihrer verschiedenen Arten. Berlin &amp; Stralsund, Gottlieb, August und lange. 3 (2): 1 - 46, pl. LI - LIV. [For dates of publication see Rathbun, 1897: 157]." type="journal article" year="1801">Herbst, 1801</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species in his reappraisal of Herbst’s taxa, but from his figure (
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai K" box="[646,797,327,351]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref6036" refString="Sakai K. 1999 a. J. F. W. Herbst-Collection of Decapod Crustacea of the Berlin Zoological Museum, with remarks on certain species. Naturalists, Tokushima Biological. Laboratory 6: 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="1999">Sakai, 1999a</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 16C), it is clear that it is the same as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1798)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[310,740,359,383]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabrus">
<emphasis box="[310,534,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Sphaerozius scabrus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius JC" box="[550,732,359,383]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" refId="ref4737" refString="Fabricius JC. 1798. Supplementum Entomologiae Systematicae Hafniae: Proft et Storch 572 p." type="book" year="1798">Fabricius, 1798</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Miers, 1880" authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1880" box="[752,1164,359,383]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pilumnidae" genus="Pilumnopeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosus">
<emphasis box="[752,1019,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Pilumnopeus granulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miers EJ" box="[1027,1164,359,383]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="304 - 317" refId="ref5682" refString="Miers EJ. 1880. On a collection of Crustacea from the Malayan Region. Part II. Telphusidea, Catometopa and Oxystomata. Annals Magazine of Natural History 5: 304 - 317." type="journal article" year="1880">Miers, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is also probably the same taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[213,1169,167,543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">
With regard to the other junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[781,886,423,447]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[781,886,423,447]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">S. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[903,933,423,447]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">viz</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1867" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" class="Malacostraca" family="Pilumnidae" genus="Actumnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudus">
<emphasis box="[950,1132,423,447]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Actumnus nudus</emphasis>
A. Milne-Edwards, 1867
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="De Man, 1899" authorityName="De Man" authorityYear="1899" box="[471,848,455,479]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Menippe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ortmanni">
<emphasis box="[471,675,455,479]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Menippe ortmanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De Man JG" box="[682,848,455,479]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="53 - 144" refId="ref5316" refString="De Man JG. 1899. Zoological results of the Dutch scientific expedition to central Borneo. The Crustacea. Part II, Brachyura. Notes from the Leyden Museum 21: 53 - 144." type="journal article" year="1899">De Man, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1894" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Menippe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexa">
<emphasis box="[859,1052,455,479]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Menippe convexa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun MJ" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="233 - 260" refId="ref5950" refString="Rathbun MJ. 1894. Description of new genera and species of crabs from the west coast of North America and the Sandwich Islands, in Scientific Results of Exploration by the US Fish Commission '' Albatross' ' No. XXIX. Proceedings of the United States National Museum [1893] 16 (933): 233 - 260." type="journal article" year="1894">Rathbun, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ward, 1941" authorityName="Ward" authorityYear="1941" box="[329,679,487,511]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oeschi">
<emphasis box="[329,537,487,511]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">Sphaerozius oeschi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ward M" box="[544,679,487,511]" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref6665" refString="Ward M. 1941. New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates 1104: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">Ward, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, all appear to be identical with what is here recognized as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[375,480,519,543]" class="Malacostraca" family="Menippidae" genus="Sphaerozius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="921" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[375,480,519,543]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="921">S. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In any case, a revision is clearly necessary
</paragraph>
